8217; Tree is restless.</em></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(5=
4,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">That&#8217;s=
 not what I tell my arborist, when I call for an evaluation. Obviously, his=
 training leans in a different direction, although he&#8217;s probably hear=
d weirder things.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);ma=
rgin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">&#8220;Branches are han=
ging over the roofline. They look unhealthy,&#8221; I say.</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;=
font-size: 16px;"><em>When it storms, when the high winds blow, they keen a=
nd wail and lash against the house.</em></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">=
&#8220;They scrape against the siding. Also, I&#8217;m worried about the sh=
ingles.&#8221;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margi=
n-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The Grandparents&#8217; Tr=
ee is a sugar maple with leaves that form a palette of soft colors in the f=
all: red, rose gold, and gold. We planted it in our front yard in 1987, aft=
er my father died. My mother-in-law had passed eight months earlier, and my=
 father-in-law, eight months before that.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"=
>This curious numerology didn&#8217;t factor into our decision to plant a s=
ingle tree as a memorial to three lives. Our yard was small; trees get big.=
 The previous owners had left us with some failing sandcherries and a thorn=
y Russian olive, which we&#8217;d taken out right away. Empty spaces begged=
 to be filled.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margi=
n-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">At first, I watered the sa=
pling diligently. But I hadn&#8217;t set it properly. The base of the trunk=
 was misaligned with the lawn&#8217;s surface. Still, it grew steadily. Twe=
nty years later, it was fully grown and glorious. But its roots cabled the =
lawn, ropy and hard. Mowing was a challenge; tripping, always a concern.</p=
><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line=
-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">My husband&#8217;s death, in April, 2023, c=
reated its own weather system. Storms no longer built predictably through h=
ot summer afternoons, releasing typical amounts of lightning and rain befor=
e moving on. They seized mornings, nights, entire days; shook them fiercely=
, brought down heavy branches and carried away good black dirt. Weeks of dr=
ought followed a wet summer. A dry winter arrived the year after the third-=
snowiest on record. The result was a hellscape of weeds, an overgrowth of v=
ines. Shrubs gone wild.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,=
55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">&#8220;Can you st=
op by this week?&#8221; I ask, staring out a window that hasn&#8217;t been =
washed in God only knows how long.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color:=
 rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">&#8220=
